Host:
^^^^
Fedora/Centos: libgit2-devel, pygame 
kivy dependencies: https://kivy.org/docs/installation/installation-linux.html:

sudo yum install \
>     make \
>     mercurial \
>     automake \
>     gcc \
>     gcc-c++ \
>     SDL_ttf-devel \
>     SDL_mixer-devel \
>     khrplatform-devel \
>     mesa-libGLES \
>     mesa-libGLES-devel \
>     gstreamer-plugins-good \
>     gstreamer \
>     gstreamer-python \
>     mtdev-devel \
>     python-devel \
>     python-pip \
>     xclip

Kivy must be compiled with SDL2, so install SDL2* libraries, and reinstall kivy with pip.
I also removed pygame and SDL libraries to make sure.
